  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A targeted model revision (mesh topology refinement in the volute region) was incorporated on 2025-11-10; the primary experimental hemolysis dataset predates this revision by approximately three weeks (dataVintage 2025-10-19). The assessment team judged the revision 'not material' to the dataset's relevance because the volute refinement altered only secondary recirculation patterns and not the blade-passage shear environment sampled by the experimental campaign. No formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed prior to submission.",
